OL,3,CMan blinded in glass attack reunited
OL,4,Cwith family after six months
OL,6,FNow, Matthew is campaigning for glass
OL,7,Fto be banned in UK bars and clubs to
OL,8,Fprevent anyone else from having to go
OL,9,Fthrough what he has suffered.
OL,11,FHe said: "It's a very easy thing to
OL,12,Ffix. mandatory ID checks and getting
OL,13,Frid of glass.
OL,15,F"If you are going out to intentionally
OL,16,Fhurt someone and you could take their
OL,17,Flife, you should get life. Luckily my
OL,18,Fpartner isn't flying over to England
OL,19,Fto bury me. Sentencing needs to be
OL,20,Fstricter."
